src/lib/components/FullCalendar.react.js.description:
DashFullCalendar – thin Dash wrapper around @fullcalendar/react.
ALL props (except the Dash house‑keeping ones) are forwarded verbatim.
No monkey‑patching of FullCalendar internals.

id.description: Unique HTML id for the calendar container.  See FullCalendar docs.

initialView.description: Name of the view the calendar shows on first load.  See FullCalendar docs.

events.description: Array, URL, or function that supplies the initial events.  See FullCalendar docs.

headerToolbar.description: Config for the top toolbar; set `false` to hide.  See FullCalendar docs.

footerToolbar.description: Config for the bottom toolbar; set `false` to hide.  See FullCalendar docs.

customButtons.description: Custom button definitions keyed by name.  See FullCalendar docs.

buttonIcons.description: Icon class strings mapped to built-in button names.  See FullCalendar docs.

buttonText.description: Override text labels for built-in buttons.  See FullCalendar docs.

themeSystem.description: Theme system to apply to built-in UI (e.g. ‘standard’, ‘bootstrap5’).  See FullCalendar docs.

height.description: Overall calendar height (`number`, ‘auto’, ‘parent’, or function).  See FullCalendar docs.

contentHeight.description: Height of the scrollable content area.  See FullCalendar docs.

aspectRatio.description: Width/height ratio when `height` is auto.  See FullCalendar docs.

expandRows.description: When `true`, rows stretch to fill vertical space.  See FullCalendar docs.

handleWindowResize.description: Recompute dimensions on window resize.  See FullCalendar docs.

windowResizeDelay.description: Debounce (ms) for the resize handler.  See FullCalendar docs.

stickyHeaderDates.description: Keep date headers fixed while scrolling.  See FullCalendar docs.

stickyFooterScrollbar.description: Show sticky scrollbar at the bottom.  See FullCalendar docs.

initialDate.description: Date the calendar navigates to on first render.  See FullCalendar docs.

validRange.description: Restricts navigation/selection to a date range.  See FullCalendar docs.

visibleRange.description: Precisely set the range of dates shown in a custom view.  See FullCalendar docs.

titleFormat.description: Date-formatting skeleton or object for the view title.  See FullCalendar docs.

locale.description: Calendar locale code (e.g. ‘en-gb’).  See FullCalendar docs.

locales.description: Array of additional locale objects to load.  See FullCalendar docs.

dir.description: Text direction: ‘ltr’ or ‘rtl’.  See FullCalendar docs.

firstDay.description: Index of week’s first day (0 = Sunday).  See FullCalendar docs.

weekends.description: Show weekend columns.  See FullCalendar docs.

hiddenDays.description: Array of day numbers to hide (0 = Sun).  See FullCalendar docs.

fixedWeekCount.description: Always render 6 weeks in month view.  See FullCalendar docs.

showNonCurrentDates.description: Render leading/trailing days in month view.  See FullCalendar docs.

dayMaxEvents.description: Collapse rows after this many events per day.  See FullCalendar docs.

dayMaxEventRows.description: Alternate way to cap events per day (rows).  See FullCalendar docs.

dayMinWidth.description: Minimum pixel width of a day column.  See FullCalendar docs.

moreLinkContent.description: Custom renderer for the ‘+ more’ link.  See FullCalendar docs.

moreLinkText.description: Text factory for the ‘+ more’ link.  See FullCalendar docs.

moreLinkWillUnmount.description: Callback before the ‘+ more’ link unmounts.  See FullCalendar docs.

dayPopoverFormat.description: Date-format skeleton for the day popover.  See FullCalendar docs.

weekNumbers.description: Show ISO week numbers down the side.  See FullCalendar docs.

weekNumberFormat.description: Formatter for week-number text.  See FullCalendar docs.

weekText.description: Short label preceding week numbers.  See FullCalendar docs.

weekTextLong.description: Long label preceding week numbers.  See FullCalendar docs.

command.description: An object specifying a command to execute on the calendar API, such as {'type': 'next'} to navigate to the next period.

setProps.description: Dash-assigned callback that should be called to report property changes to Dash, registered automatically.
